{"debug": {"version": 3.1}, "status": "OK", "results": {"api_timestamp": "1481481314", "totalCommentsFound": 3824, "totalCommentsReturned": 25, "comments": [{"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 290, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11917752, "rgt": 291, "userDisplayName": "Steve Singer", "createDate": "1401501619", "userID": 8562342, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508809", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Chicago", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505209", "commentSequence": 11917752, "commentBody": "Well, if the Greater Fool Theory still works, and I suspect it does, Mr. Ballmer's foray into a business he doesn't really know too well marks a market top; just one of many.<br/><br/>Just one red flag after another is all I see these days.<br/><br/>Look out below.", "recommendationCount": 4}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 292, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11917755, "rgt": 293, "userDisplayName": "Vermonter", "createDate": "1401501678", "userID": 3941029, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508811", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Vermont", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505211", "commentSequence": 11917755, "commentBody": "A fool and his money are soon parted...", "recommendationCount": 0}, {"assetID": 3402816, "replies": [], "lft": 17, "assetURL": "http://nocera.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/05/30/the-gun-report-may-30-2014/", "parentID": 11916456, "commentID": 11917758, "rgt": 18, "userDisplayName": "paul", "createDate": "1401501720", "userID": 47231823, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508816", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "blyn", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505216", "commentSequence": 11917758, "commentBody": "HDNY...well worded post...Lincolnesque....<br/><br/>Malcolm/Charlotte gave you a starting point...<br/><br/>Listen to Malcolm/Charlotte..he has the answers to our gun crisis...and your immediate question.....", "recommendationCount": 2}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 294, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11917784, "rgt": 295, "userDisplayName": "dairubo", "createDate": "1401502231", "userID": 44811612, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508818", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "MN", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505218", "commentSequence": 11917784, "commentBody": "This is merely a trade of unearned assets between the Ballmer family and the Sterling family.  The important thing to note is that neither party to this trade has made a contribution to society large enough to justify their wealth.  Sure, their wealth was was legally acquired, but who made the rules?  We need to restructure our attitudes toward the accumulation of wealth.", "recommendationCount": 12}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 296, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11917798, "rgt": 297, "userDisplayName": "troublemaker", "createDate": "1401502513", "userID": 4050468, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508826", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "new york, ny usa", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505226", "commentSequence": 11917798, "commentBody": "I read comments talking about free-market capitalism.  How is any business done in the NBA or other professional sports involving public subsidy of a sports arena free market?  An owner can be forced to sell a team? How on earth is that free market?", "recommendationCount": 2}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": {"comments": [{"recommendedFlag": 0, "parentID": 11917801, "replies": [], "commentID": 11918306, "trusted": 0, "userDisplayName": "Byron", "createDate": "1401510411", "userID": 26985752, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401512698", "userTitle": "NULL", "recommendations": 0, "editorsSelection": false, "parentUserDisplayName": "Greg Ceo", "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Washington", "depth": 1, "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401509098", "commentSequence": 11918306, "commentBody": "There has been a lot of serious money already spent by Seattle business interests in an attempt to get a new basketball arena built ... for the purpose of luring an NBA team back up here. There are many here who greatly miss the game."}]}, "lft": 298, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11917801, "rgt": 301, "userDisplayName": "Greg Ceo", "createDate": "1401502543", "userID": 47765011, "replyCount": 1, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508837", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Savannah, GA", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505237", "commentSequence": 11917801, "commentBody": "Anyone wanna bet that the next installment of this story is Steve Ballmer asking Seattle for a great big public subsidy for a new arena? Because he can afford $2 billion for a team, and expect to soon take in $100 million a year in TV revenue alone, but the taxpayers will be expected to pay for an arena, told it's great economic development but the team can't afford it themselves, and then they'll get lots of minimum wage jobs selling hot dogs in return for the public investment. Stay tuned.", "recommendationCount": 10}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 271, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917279, "commentID": 11917810, "rgt": 272, "userDisplayName": "John", "createDate": "1401502745", "userID": 69444545, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508839", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "New York, NY", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505239", "commentSequence": 11917810, "commentBody": "Because he started at Microsoft in 1980. Their IPO was in 1986.", "recommendationCount": 0}, {"assetID": 3402716, "replies": [], "lft": 237, "assetURL": "http://nocera.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/05/29/the-gun-report-may-29-2014/", "parentID": 11912571, "commentID": 11917773, "rgt": 238, "userDisplayName": "paul", "createDate": "1401502064", "userID": 47231823, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508841", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "blyn", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505241", "commentSequence": 11917773, "commentBody": "Oh my God...do we have a seminal moment here??....Steverino the fiery anti gun poster agreeing with Malcolm/Charlotte.<br/><br/>What hath Jen  wrought?<br/><br/>Well written Malcolm/Charlotte.another no brainer from Malcolm.....and well retorted Steverino...", "recommendationCount": 1}, {"asset