e": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Providence, RI", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505248", "commentSequence": 11917833, "commentBody": "Then let's hope the recipients of the $2billion heed your advice.", "recommendationCount": 0}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 273, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917279, "commentID": 11917846, "rgt": 274, "userDisplayName": "richard schumacher", "createDate": "1401503302", "userID": 18868541, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508852", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "united states", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505252", "commentSequence": 11917846, "commentBody": "Google is your friend.  M$ stock has split 9 times, some at 2:1, some at 3:2.  The net effect has been to multiply each original share into 288 current shares. ", "recommendationCount": 0}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 302, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11917875, "rgt": 303, "userDisplayName": "J Kremer", "createDate": "1401503616", "userID": 25172527, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508856", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Minneapolis", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505256", "commentSequence": 11917875, "commentBody": "And all subsidized with taxpayer financed stadiums and tax-deductible corporate tickets--where they talk \"business\".", "recommendationCount": 4}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 304, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11917946, "rgt": 305, "userDisplayName": "Dick Diamond", "createDate": "1401504593", "userID": 37337225, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508866", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Bay City, Oregon", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505266", "commentSequence": 11917946, "commentBody": "So what?  Would there be this talk about the profit made in the selling of a steel company?    A drug company?  Any company that is privately owned?  This is a company that is part of a cartel of 30 people who have more power over a \"sport\" in this country, as to where is plays, who owns it, where it doesn't play, etc. than OPEC in oil.  We are the suckers who pay for the arenas and are willing to pay big bucks to see the gladiators in the arena.  ", "recommendationCount": 4}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 306, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11917997, "rgt": 307, "userDisplayName": "RS", "createDate": "1401505282", "userID": 66742458, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508868", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Philly", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505268", "commentSequence": 11917997, "commentBody": "Sterling wins.", "recommendationCount": 3}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 261, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917278, "commentID": 11918003, "rgt": 262, "userDisplayName": "Bronzi", "createDate": "1401505311", "userID": 43975511, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508875", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "NJ", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505276", "commentSequence": 11918003, "commentBody": "Cablevision charges a$4.95 sports fees. I dont watch any of the sports channel, but can't get away from it without giving up cable. Expect costs to go up when NBA broadcast rights are up for renegotiation. ", "recommendationCount": 1}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 308, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11918012, "rgt": 309, "userDisplayName": "Steve Hunter", "createDate": "1401505470", "userID": 44499492, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508878", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Seattle", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505278", "commentSequence": 11918012, "commentBody": "I can think of a lot better ways to spend $2 billion. ", "recommendationCount": 2}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 265, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917481, "commentID": 11918015, "rgt": 266, "userDisplayName": "DMV74", "createDate": "1401505510", "userID": 64652641, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508882", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Washington, DC", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505282", "commentSequence": 11918015, "commentBody": "Why is it his job to send other people's kids to college. Do you set aside some of your salary to help defray the college cost of others? You may not be able to pay their entire tuition but could pay for books or a new lap top. Why must he give his money to others and do you actually know his philanthropical giving?", "recommendationCount": 2}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 243, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917394, "commentID": 11918018, "rgt": 244, "userDisplayName": "Tim D.", "createDate": "1401505535", "userID": 11685531, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508884", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Los Angeles, CA", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505284", "commentSequence": 11918018, "commentBody": "Exactly right. ", "recommendationCount": 2}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 247, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917190, "commentID": 11918026, "rgt": 248, "userDisplayName": "David", "createDate": "1401505625", "userID": 67523392, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508888", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Portland", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505288", "commentSequence": 11918026, "commentBody": "The money police should come in at about $1 billion, I would say. When a society becomes as economically imbalanced as our is, we all have the right to question. Not questioning is the problem.", "recommendationCount": 5}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 173, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917112, "commentID": 11918027, "rgt": 174, "userDisplayName": "Bronzi", "createDate": "1401505632", "userID": 43975511, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508894", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "NJ", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505294", "commentSequence": 11918027, "commentBody": "You have to sound angry to be racist?  Its not the loud bigot one must fear. Its the seemingly \"normal\" ones that are the real ones to fear. ", "recommendationCount": 2}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 249, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917190, "commentID": 11918074, "rgt": 250, "userDisplayName": "jombee", "createDate": "1401506378", "userID": 32426302, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508913", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "USA", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505313", "commentSequence": 11918074, "commentBody": "It's not a right, it's a pleasure. <br/><br/>Anybody can question what anybody does. And you're right, nobody is required to spend their money on something they don't want to after taxes. Doesn't mean it's right, doesn't mean it's ok, doesn't mean it's stupid, or immoral, or that the money could be spent on something more worthwhile than a bunch of billionaire's hobbies. <br/><br/>Congrats on your pretty decent salary though. Enjoy the baby clothes.  ", "recommendationCount": 2}, {"assetID": 3402716, "replies": [], "lft": 103, "assetURL": "http://nocera.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/05/29/the-gun-report-may-29-2014/", "parentID": 11908542, "commentID": 11918169, "rgt": 104, "userDisplayName": "Clairette Rose", "createDate": "1401507659", "userID": 5967320, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508918", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "San Francisco", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505318", "commentSequence": 11918169, "commentBody": "@QP --<br/><br/>I'll buy that.  As long as the NRA is campaigning everywhere on a platform of fear of \"bad guys\" who can only be dealt with by \"good guys\" with guns, people will indeed purchase guns.<br/><br/>And while the NRA offers many safety classes, so long as that same NRA blocks legislation that would mandate safety training as a prerequisite to gun purchasing, well, then, yes, the NRA is responsible. ", "recommendationCount": 4}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 310, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": null, "commentID": 11918087, "rgt": 311, "userDisplayName": "Iver Thompson", "createDate": "1401506497", "userID": 37475504, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "<br/>", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508924", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 1, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Pasadena, CA", "commentType": "comment", "updateDate": "1401505324", "commentSequence": 11918087, "commentBody": "As the Upshot points out, the overinflated price being paid is unprecedented and never would have come about without the scandal and all the publicity it has garnered the Clippers and Sterling.  So now Balmer not only gets courtside seats, but the recognition of conceivably being the white knight on horseback riding in to save we poor Angelenos from the terrible and racist ugly scourge known as Donald T. Sterling.<br/><br/>It's almost as if on some level this whole deal were scripted to make it appear we poor huddled masses need these rich white guys to save us from all the world's woes.  These \"guys\" really know how to each others backs.<br/><br/>Sterling and Balmer are probably toasting each other and laughing at us all from up in their penthouses.  And were the rest of the NBA owners in on the planning of this as well?<br/><br/>Silver's announcement that the league meant to \"punish\" Sterling for his racism and offensive comments?  That's even a bigger laugh!  If we, the public, had our heads together, there wouldn't be a single seat occupied in any of those monuments to decadence and greed called professional sport stadiums, other than the fat-cat owners themselves and their mistresses.   ", "recommendationCount": 11}, {"assetID": 3402797, "replies": [], "lft": 275, "assetURL": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/31/sports/basketball/steven-a-ballmers-2-billion-play-for-clippers-is-a-big-bet-on-the-nba.html", "parentID": 11917279, "commentID": 11918117, "rgt": 276, "userDisplayName": "John", "createDate": "1401506948", "userID": 13803738, "replyCount": 0, "commentTitle": "n/a", "status": "approved", "approveDate": "1401508927", "userTitle": "NULL", "editorsSelection": 0, "statusID": 2, "userURL": "NULL", "userLocation": "Los Angeles", "commentType": "userReply", "updateDate": "1401505327", "commentSequence": 11918117, "commentBody": "Have you ever heard of dividends?", "recommendationCount": 0}]}, "copyright": "Copyright (c) 2016 The New York Times Company.  All Rights Reserved."}